WEBVTT

00:10.594 --> 00:12.012
♪ You could do it solo ♪

00:12.012 --> 00:14.097
♪ But then you'd be all by yourself ♪

00:14.097 --> 00:16.433
♪ Yo! So it'd be more fun
To share this one ♪

00:16.433 --> 00:17.893
♪ With someone else ♪

00:17.893 --> 00:21.688
♪ Together we will soar
Across the sky and beyond ♪

00:21.688 --> 00:23.023
♪ So turn up your voice ♪

00:23.815 --> 00:25.734
♪ Stand up and sing along! ♪

00:25.734 --> 00:27.027
♪ All different voices ♪

00:27.027 --> 00:27.945
♪ Everybody now! ♪

00:27.945 --> 00:29.404
♪ Our melodies ringing ♪

00:29.404 --> 00:31.156
♪ We're livin' in harmony ♪

00:31.156 --> 00:33.158
♪ Yeah, we're livin' in harmony ♪

00:33.158 --> 00:37.079
♪ Our song is much stronger
With every Troll singing ♪

00:37.079 --> 00:39.540
♪ We're livin' in harmony ♪♪

00:41.041 --> 00:43.001
♪

00:45.921 --> 00:50.217
POPPY: <i>It's the dream of every Troll</i>
<i>to test their mettle in the ring</i>

00:50.884 --> 00:53.679
<i>to send their opponent</i>
<i>tumbling to the mat...</i>

00:55.097 --> 00:56.098
[ fart ]

00:56.098 --> 00:58.350
<i>...with uncontrollable laughter.</i>

00:58.350 --> 01:01.186
[ laugh ]

01:01.186 --> 01:02.271
[ bell rings ]

01:02.271 --> 01:05.983
<i>It's the Great TrollsTopia</i>
<i>Laugh Out Bout.</i>

01:05.983 --> 01:08.819
<i>Two Trolls enter, one Troll laughs!</i>

01:08.819 --> 01:11.071
<i>And then everyone gets ice cream.</i>

01:11.655 --> 01:13.782
[ cheering ]

01:13.782 --> 01:16.910
So, each tribe nominates
one champion to compete.

01:16.910 --> 01:20.622
First Troll to knock the other Troll out
with a laugh wins the match.

01:20.622 --> 01:22.249
And at the end of all the matches,

01:22.249 --> 01:25.961
last Troll standing takes home
the coveted Golden Chatter Teeth!

01:25.961 --> 01:27.796
[ teeth chattering ]

01:27.796 --> 01:29.881
May the funniest Troll win!

01:29.881 --> 01:32.467
[ cheering ]

01:32.467 --> 01:33.677
COOPER:
Woo!

01:34.803 --> 01:36.138
LOWNOTE:
Uh, Cooper...

01:36.138 --> 01:38.557
We have something
we'd like to discuss with you.

01:38.557 --> 01:41.935
‐ Oh. Is it about the sparkle melons
stuck on my feet?

01:43.228 --> 01:44.730
[ laugh ]

01:44.730 --> 01:45.856
So stylish!

01:46.898 --> 01:47.816
‐ What?

01:48.650 --> 01:51.486
Now we have two things
we want to discuss with you.

01:51.903 --> 01:53.697
‐ Hmmm...

01:54.364 --> 01:55.991
Poppy! Poppy!

01:57.034 --> 02:00.537
Guess what?
The Funk Tribe has asked me, Cooper,

02:00.537 --> 02:03.623
to represent them in the Laugh Out Bout!

02:04.124 --> 02:06.710
‐ Wow, Cooper, what an honor!

02:06.710 --> 02:07.753
‐ I know!

02:08.003 --> 02:10.881
This is the biggest responsibility
the tribe has given me

02:10.881 --> 02:13.258
since I found out
I was born a Funk Troll...

02:13.842 --> 02:15.552
I just want to make them so proud.

02:16.887 --> 02:20.515
‐ Oh, Cooper, you definitely will.
You're the funniest Troll I know!

02:20.932 --> 02:21.850
‐ True...

02:22.059 --> 02:24.019
But there's just one small problem.

02:24.353 --> 02:27.272
[ laughing ]

02:27.272 --> 02:30.317
‐ Oh, is it that you laugh at everything?

02:30.734 --> 02:32.653
‐ I laugh at everything!

02:33.695 --> 02:36.448
Not exactly
the best personality quirk to have

02:36.448 --> 02:39.743
whilst participating
in a "don't laugh" competition.

02:39.743 --> 02:41.244
[ laughing ]

02:41.244 --> 02:42.704
I am doomed!

02:43.914 --> 02:45.749
‐ No, we can fix that.

02:45.916 --> 02:48.710
Whenever I feel the giggles comin' on
before a big speech,

02:48.710 --> 02:50.754
I just take a moment and get 'em all out.

02:50.754 --> 02:51.672
Like so...

02:51.672 --> 02:52.589
[ clears throat ]

02:52.589 --> 02:58.595
[ laughing ]

03:01.139 --> 03:02.557
[ sigh ]

03:03.642 --> 03:06.770
‐ Oh! I see. So like...

03:06.770 --> 03:12.818
[ laughing ]

03:25.163 --> 03:26.957
‐ And that's when it hit me,

03:26.957 --> 03:30.585
all this time,
the bunker has kinda been a metaphor...

03:31.420 --> 03:32.462
for my heart.

03:33.213 --> 03:35.966
‐ Yes. Oh, yes, Branch...

03:36.508 --> 03:37.634
that's huge.

03:37.634 --> 03:43.640
[ laughing ]

03:47.185 --> 03:49.104
[ sigh ]

03:50.355 --> 03:51.273
[ Poppy gasps ]

03:51.273 --> 03:53.442
So, you, you got it out?

03:54.151 --> 03:56.403
‐ Not even close!

03:57.446 --> 03:59.364
[ Poppy groans ]

03:59.364 --> 04:00.866
[ teeth chattering ]

04:01.450 --> 04:02.951
It's no use, Poppy.

04:02.951 --> 04:06.037
My laughter is like a river,
it never stops flowing.

04:06.455 --> 04:08.165
And sometimes there's fish in it.

04:09.291 --> 04:10.125
Oh!

04:10.834 --> 04:11.751
[ Cooper sighs ]

04:11.751 --> 04:15.630
I guess I gotta go tell Lownote
to pick another Funk Troll.

04:16.047 --> 04:18.133
‐ No, Cooper, we can figure this out.

04:18.425 --> 04:21.219
There's gotta be some way
to get you ready for the bout.

04:21.595 --> 04:24.639
‐ Did someone say
they need a humor expert?

04:26.141 --> 04:27.684
‐ No, we didn't.
‐ No, we didn't.

04:28.143 --> 04:29.853
‐ Hm, unfortunate.

04:29.853 --> 04:32.522
That would have been
far more dramatic if you had.

04:32.898 --> 04:35.984
‐ Well, we'll take whatever help
you can offer, Laguna, but...

04:36.234 --> 04:38.195
you are a humor expert?

04:38.320 --> 04:43.784
‐ Indeed. Which is ironic,
given that most Trolls find me quite dry,

04:45.660 --> 04:49.498
which is also ironic
given that I live underwater.

04:50.040 --> 04:51.958
‐ Oh...
‐ Oh...

04:53.710 --> 04:58.507
‐ Now, as with all things,
the key to comedy is research.

04:59.382 --> 05:00.592
‐ Research?
‐ Research?

05:00.592 --> 05:04.095
‐ Oh, yes, for laughter
is simply an involuntary reaction

05:04.095 --> 05:06.306
to that which is delightfully unexpected,

05:06.306 --> 05:08.600
like a funny face, a silly sound,

05:08.600 --> 05:11.311
or the most powerful form
of humor of all...

05:11.645 --> 05:14.231
a delicious pun.

05:16.817 --> 05:18.235
‐ I think she likes puns.

05:18.443 --> 05:21.071
‐Ergo, the key to not laughing at the bout

05:21.071 --> 05:24.115
is to learn each opponents'
comedy style in advance,

05:24.324 --> 05:27.244
thereby eliminating
the element of surprise.

05:27.536 --> 05:30.580
‐Oh, I am very much on board
for this exercise.

05:30.997 --> 05:34.918
Provided it involves
some sort of slide projector...?

05:35.710 --> 05:38.755
Oh, ho, ho, we are cookin' now!

05:39.172 --> 05:44.052
‐ First up, we have the Pop Tribe
Laugh Out Champion, Guy Diamond...

05:44.553 --> 05:48.640
<i>Guy's style is to Knock Knock you out</i>
<i>with a Knock Knock joke.</i>

05:48.974 --> 05:51.184
‐ Hey, Cooper. Knock, knock.

05:51.184 --> 05:52.769
‐ Who's there?
‐ Boo.

05:53.186 --> 05:54.187
‐ Boo who?

05:54.187 --> 05:57.607
‐ Don't cry, Daddy's friend Cooper!
It's just a joke!

05:58.024 --> 06:00.318
[ laughing ]

06:00.318 --> 06:01.653
‐ One, two...

06:04.030 --> 06:05.907
LAGUNA:
<i>So, if you want to defeat him,</i>

06:05.907 --> 06:08.034
<i>you have to beat him to the punchline.</i>

06:08.326 --> 06:10.161
TINY DIAMOND:
Oh, back for more, huh?

06:10.161 --> 06:12.289
Okay, well then, knock, kno‐‐

06:12.289 --> 06:13.582
‐ Interrupting cow!

06:13.582 --> 06:14.791
[ gasp ]

06:14.791 --> 06:17.669
‐ How did you know we were going to say‐‐?
‐ Moo!

06:18.378 --> 06:20.589
[ laughing ]

06:20.589 --> 06:23.216
‐ One, two, three...

06:23.216 --> 06:26.094
that's an L. O. L. K. O.!

06:26.094 --> 06:32.100
[ cheering ]

06:32.517 --> 06:35.604
‐ Cooper, you used
the research flawlessly!

06:35.604 --> 06:37.439
We were very impressed!

06:37.439 --> 06:40.317
‐ Yeah, and we weren't the only ones.

06:40.317 --> 06:41.818
[ cheering ]

06:41.818 --> 06:43.570
‐ C'mon, Funk Tribe!

06:43.570 --> 06:47.157
Let's give it up for our champion, Cooper!

06:47.157 --> 06:49.075
[ cheering ]

06:49.075 --> 06:53.121
♪ He's got your number on speed dial ♪

06:53.121 --> 06:54.998
♪ First you'll be grinnin' ♪

06:54.998 --> 06:57.417
♪ Then you gonna crack a smile, woo! ♪

06:57.417 --> 07:01.463
♪ Before you know it
You're gonna lose control ♪

07:01.463 --> 07:05.216
♪ You're gonna blow it
Laughing rollin' on the floor ♪

07:05.216 --> 07:07.177
♪ Cuz Cooper spins super ♪

07:07.177 --> 07:09.346
♪ Slapstick side splitting humor ♪

07:09.346 --> 07:13.350
♪ He's silly, straight killing us
With ridiculous bloopers ♪

07:13.350 --> 07:15.602
♪ He's our funny, funky, fabulous ♪

07:15.602 --> 07:17.520
♪ First place winner champion ♪

07:17.520 --> 07:19.856
♪ He's got jokes so fresh
He will impress ♪

07:19.856 --> 07:21.941
♪ This baby was born to win ♪

07:21.941 --> 07:24.027
♪ Try not to laugh, but you won't last ♪

07:24.027 --> 07:25.945
♪ He's hilarious till the end ♪

07:25.945 --> 07:28.156
♪ He's our funny, funky, fabulous ♪

07:28.156 --> 07:29.699
♪ First place winner champion ♪

07:29.699 --> 07:31.409
♪ And he was born to win ♪♪

07:33.328 --> 07:35.622
♪

07:35.622 --> 07:37.540
<i>‐ Get ready, TrollsTopia!</i>

07:37.540 --> 07:41.294
<i>'Cuz it's time for the final bout!</i>

07:41.628 --> 07:44.130
‐ Only one match left
to win it all, Cooper.

07:44.130 --> 07:46.049
You've joked masterfully!

07:46.049 --> 07:49.594
‐ Indeed he has!
Ha, ha, I just knew you were

07:49.594 --> 07:51.805
the right Funk Troll for this, Cooper!

07:52.097 --> 07:53.014
[ gasp ]

07:53.014 --> 07:55.975
‐ Thank you, Lownote!
That means the world to me.

07:56.434 --> 07:58.269
<i>‐ In this corner...</i>

07:58.269 --> 08:03.942
<i>put your hands together for Cooper!</i>

08:03.942 --> 08:05.944
[ cheering ]

08:05.944 --> 08:07.779
‐ Well, I'm on, Lownote.

08:07.779 --> 08:10.865
But don't worry,
I can take on any challenger,

08:10.865 --> 08:14.369
as long as I've got
coach Laguna TidePool by my side!

08:15.245 --> 08:20.208
<i>‐ And in the opposite corner,</i>
<i>Laguna TidePool!</i>

08:20.208 --> 08:22.335
[ cheering ]

08:22.794 --> 08:23.712
[ gasp ]

08:23.712 --> 08:25.505
‐ Well, that's my cue.

08:26.548 --> 08:27.507
‐ Laguna?
‐ Laguna?

08:27.507 --> 08:28.341
‐ Yes?

08:28.675 --> 08:31.219
‐ My final challenger is you?

08:31.511 --> 08:33.680
‐ Of course, was that not clear?

08:33.972 --> 08:34.806
‐ No!
‐ No!

08:35.223 --> 08:36.349
‐ Oh, well, good luck.

08:37.434 --> 08:40.478
[ panting ]

08:40.478 --> 08:42.522
[ Cooper screams ]

08:42.522 --> 08:44.441
‐Whoa, whoa, whoa, Cooper! It's okay!

08:44.441 --> 08:46.401
‐ No, it's not, Poppy!

08:46.401 --> 08:48.903
If she knew how to beat
all those other Trolls,

08:48.903 --> 08:51.156
she knows how to beat me too!

08:51.614 --> 08:54.034
I shoulda never let
the Funk Trolls pick me...!

08:54.242 --> 08:55.910
[ Cooper screams ]

08:55.910 --> 08:57.495
‐ C'mon, Cooper, hang in there.

08:57.787 --> 09:00.206
Remember what Laguna
taught you about research.

09:00.206 --> 09:03.334
If we think, I'm sure we've learned
something about her

09:03.334 --> 09:05.170
that you could use to your advantage.

09:07.172 --> 09:08.214
[ wail ]

09:08.214 --> 09:10.884
‐ I can't think of anything, can you?
‐ No!

09:11.051 --> 09:13.136
[ Poppy and Cooper scream ]

09:14.721 --> 09:17.599
‐ Apologies, Cooper,
but I'm afraid making me laugh

09:17.599 --> 09:19.309
will be quite impossible.

09:19.559 --> 09:23.104
I know every silly gag you'll try,
even before you do.

09:23.730 --> 09:25.023
‐ Uh...

09:25.398 --> 09:26.649
Oh, what if I‐‐

09:26.649 --> 09:28.151
‐ Pull a flute out of your nose?

09:28.985 --> 09:31.529
♪

09:31.529 --> 09:32.655
[ laugh ]

09:33.490 --> 09:35.200
‐ No! Or maybe I could‐‐

09:35.200 --> 09:37.660
‐ Ride a unicycle
while juggling rubber duckies?

09:37.660 --> 09:41.247
♪

09:41.247 --> 09:45.001
[ laughing ]

09:45.001 --> 09:45.835
‐ Huh?

09:46.836 --> 09:50.131
<i>‐ And now, the final blow...</i>

09:51.716 --> 09:53.718
POPPY:
<i>Joke back, Cooper!</i>

09:54.385 --> 09:56.054
<i>Joke back!</i>

09:57.472 --> 09:59.974
<i>Remember what Laguna</i>
<i>taught you about research.</i>

09:59.974 --> 10:02.393
<i>I'm sure we've learned</i>
<i>something about her</i>

10:02.393 --> 10:05.105
<i>that you could use to your advantage...</i>

10:06.272 --> 10:07.107
[ gasp ]

10:07.899 --> 10:10.443
‐ Or the most powerful
form of humor of all...

10:10.652 --> 10:13.029
a delicious pun.

10:14.322 --> 10:15.990
‐ Oh!

10:16.866 --> 10:21.621
‐ Do not despair that the Techno Tribe
will be taking home the trophy, Cooper.

10:21.621 --> 10:23.748
You are a very funny Troll.

10:24.249 --> 10:26.709
‐ Yeah? Well, it takes one...

10:27.210 --> 10:28.837
to tech‐know one.

10:29.379 --> 10:30.213
[ gasp ]

10:32.006 --> 10:35.301
[ cheering ]

10:36.344 --> 10:37.178
‐ You...

10:37.428 --> 10:41.057
you used a delicious pun against me!

10:43.059 --> 10:45.353
‐ Gill‐ty as charged.

10:45.937 --> 10:47.021
Gill‐ty...

10:47.355 --> 10:48.398
As in gills...

10:48.731 --> 10:50.108
'Cause you've got gills...

10:50.775 --> 10:54.362
[ laughing ]

10:54.362 --> 11:00.034
‐ No, I can't resist
the pure comedic perfection...

11:00.326 --> 11:01.536
‐ Oh, I know.

11:01.536 --> 11:03.997
You didn't expect my word play to be so...

11:04.497 --> 11:06.666
pun‐ishing.

11:06.916 --> 11:07.876
[ gasp ]

11:08.334 --> 11:12.172
‐ It seems as though the student
has become the master.

11:12.172 --> 11:15.967
[ laughing ]

11:15.967 --> 11:19.596
‐ One, two, three! LOL!

11:20.305 --> 11:22.056
[ cheering ]

11:22.056 --> 11:25.185
We have a new Laugh Out Bout champion!

11:25.185 --> 11:26.936
[ cheer ]

11:26.936 --> 11:29.814
‐ Cooper! You did us proud, baby!

11:29.814 --> 11:31.608
You did us proud!

11:31.608 --> 11:34.402
EVERYONE:
Cooper! Cooper! Cooper!

11:34.402 --> 11:35.320
[ gasp ]

11:35.320 --> 11:38.198
[ teeth chattering ]

11:40.200 --> 11:42.202
♪

11:42.744 --> 11:46.664
♪

11:46.664 --> 11:48.791
GUST:
Hair‐aldine!

11:48.791 --> 11:49.667
[ gasp ]

11:49.667 --> 11:54.005
Hair‐aldine Groundwater,
look what that product of yours

11:54.005 --> 11:55.840
has done to your sister's hair.

11:55.840 --> 11:59.260
Holdin' its shape against gravity itself.

11:59.260 --> 12:02.430
Why, a dang twister
couldn't move a strand!

12:04.182 --> 12:05.892
It ain't natural!

12:05.892 --> 12:08.645
‐ But pa‐pa. Don't you see?

12:09.520 --> 12:12.315
My new invention will change the world.

12:12.523 --> 12:14.359
I call it "hair..."

12:15.318 --> 12:16.236
Uh...

12:16.861 --> 12:17.695
"Spray."

12:18.655 --> 12:19.656
Ugh.

12:19.989 --> 12:21.366
Sorry, Holly.

12:21.366 --> 12:23.451
Told you acting really isn't my thing...

12:23.451 --> 12:24.786
Ran out of room on my hands!

12:25.578 --> 12:26.496
[ Holly sighs ]

12:26.496 --> 12:27.997
<i>‐ It's fine, sugar.</i>

12:27.997 --> 12:31.668
<i>I just appreciate you helpin' out</i>
<i>while I continue to do auditions.</i>

12:32.210 --> 12:33.628
<i>Take five, y'all!</i>

12:33.836 --> 12:36.339
[ indiscernible conversation ]

12:36.339 --> 12:39.467
‐ Still no luck finding someone
to play the lead role, huh?

12:39.467 --> 12:42.845
‐ Oh, Poppy,
Hair‐aldine Groundwater is my hero!

12:43.179 --> 12:48.226
She overcame enormous odds
to become the inventor of hairspray.

12:48.518 --> 12:50.520
So, whoever plays her in my musical

12:50.520 --> 12:55.149
has to have an independent spirit,
a fire in their eyes.

12:55.566 --> 12:59.070
But I just can't seem to find
the right Troll to play the part.

12:59.070 --> 12:59.904
[ trolls gasps ]

12:59.904 --> 13:00.863
‐ Huh?
‐ Huh?

13:04.993 --> 13:10.248
‐ Here's your order. But, Val,
squeezable cheese on ice cream?

13:10.456 --> 13:11.874
It ain't natural!

13:13.084 --> 13:14.085
‐ I know.

13:14.502 --> 13:15.795
[ trolls gasp ]

13:18.006 --> 13:20.216
[ laughing ]

13:21.426 --> 13:24.262
‐ She has such an independent spirit!

13:25.179 --> 13:27.557
TROLL:
Look at the fire in her eyes!

13:28.224 --> 13:29.100
[ gasp ]

13:29.475 --> 13:31.102
‐ My Hair‐aldine...

13:32.603 --> 13:37.358
[ laughing ]

13:37.859 --> 13:41.279
‐ You want me to do musical theater?

13:41.279 --> 13:43.614
‐ Yes, I think you'd be very good at‐‐

13:43.614 --> 13:48.619
[ laughing ]

13:48.619 --> 13:49.996
‐ I'm sorry. I'm sorry. Uh.

13:50.246 --> 13:53.916
But I would never be caught
dancin' and singin' to a bunch of Trolls.

13:53.916 --> 13:56.252
‐ Uh, you do that all the time.

13:57.378 --> 13:58.629
‐ Huh. Very true.

13:59.964 --> 14:02.967
But my rock concerts are edgy and awesome.

14:03.384 --> 14:05.553
Musical theater is, uh...

14:05.803 --> 14:06.721
not.

14:06.721 --> 14:10.141
‐ Please, Val.
I've worked so hard on this musical.

14:10.141 --> 14:11.225
If you say no...

14:11.809 --> 14:13.686
I'm gonna have to go with Synth...

14:14.270 --> 14:15.646
[ laugh ]

14:15.646 --> 14:18.191
‐ And you definitely don't want that, yo!

14:19.233 --> 14:21.277
‐ Sorry, Holly. Not my thing.

14:21.277 --> 14:22.987
Thundershock out!

14:23.696 --> 14:26.032
PYROTECHNIC VOICE:
<i>Thundershock out!</i>

14:27.158 --> 14:28.034
[ sigh ]

14:28.409 --> 14:30.203
‐ Well, it was worth a shot...

14:30.745 --> 14:33.331
‐ Val, wait! You're just gonna say "no"?

14:33.331 --> 14:36.626
Shouldn't you take a second
to think about what this means to Holly?

14:37.126 --> 14:39.087
‐ Yeah, I probably should...

14:40.254 --> 14:41.464
but yeah, no way.

14:41.964 --> 14:42.799
‐ Ugh.

14:43.132 --> 14:44.175
Okay!

14:44.467 --> 14:47.053
I hoped the power of friendship
would convince you,

14:47.053 --> 14:49.722
but since you clearly need
more motivation,

14:49.722 --> 14:52.266
how about the power of friendship and...

14:53.351 --> 14:55.728
a pass to skip the line
at the Big Squeeze?

14:56.062 --> 14:56.938
[ gasp ]

14:57.647 --> 14:59.273
‐ I love the Big Squeeze!

14:59.565 --> 15:01.567
You can see everything from up there!

15:02.068 --> 15:04.237
Woo!

15:04.237 --> 15:06.989
Ha! I can see all the way to Rock Hollow!

15:06.989 --> 15:07.990
Wooo!

15:07.990 --> 15:09.158
[ laugh ]

15:09.909 --> 15:12.286
Hey, get your hands off my guitar!

15:12.286 --> 15:13.579
ROCK TROLL:
Sorry, Val!

15:13.871 --> 15:15.456
‐ You've got a deal, Popsqueak!

15:15.456 --> 15:17.166
Thundershock back in!

15:18.000 --> 15:20.670
PYROTECHNIC VOICE:
<i>Thundershock back in!</i>

15:21.337 --> 15:22.171
[ gasp ]

15:23.089 --> 15:25.049
‐ Hot dang, Val!

15:25.216 --> 15:28.970
Does that glimmerin' pyro mean
what I think it means?

15:28.970 --> 15:30.555
You'll play Hair‐aldine?

15:30.930 --> 15:32.890
‐ Just tell me what you want me to do.

15:33.057 --> 15:35.184
‐ Woo hoo!

15:35.351 --> 15:36.686
Ready to get to wardrobe?

15:37.228 --> 15:38.062
‐ Yes?

15:39.438 --> 15:40.356
No.

15:40.356 --> 15:43.401
‐ Now, Val, I know this isn't your style,

15:43.401 --> 15:46.154
but this is the kind of dress
Hair‐aldine wore.

15:46.154 --> 15:49.782
That said, we can always modify it
so you're more comfortable.

15:49.782 --> 15:50.950
‐ Oh. Really?

15:50.950 --> 15:53.494
‐ Of course, we could bring it in a bit!

15:53.995 --> 15:56.497
Or add fun accessories! Or...

15:56.497 --> 16:01.460
♪

16:01.460 --> 16:02.962
‐ Or you could rip it to shreds,

16:02.962 --> 16:05.673
erasing hours of our blood,
sweat and tears.

16:05.965 --> 16:08.885
‐ Rock on! Wardrobe's done, what's next?

16:09.969 --> 16:10.970
Ugh.

16:11.220 --> 16:14.765
‐ Okay, Val, in theater you gotta get used

16:14.765 --> 16:17.977
to wearing heavy make‐up
to help aid your performance...

16:18.477 --> 16:19.312
‐ Eh?

16:19.896 --> 16:21.147
‐ Eh, I'm cool with that.

16:21.772 --> 16:23.316
‐ Oh... Well, good.

16:23.608 --> 16:25.818
‐ Yeah... Hard Rock Trolls
do the same thing.

16:25.818 --> 16:26.861
[ hiss ]

16:26.861 --> 16:27.695
[ gasps ]

16:28.446 --> 16:29.906
What? Not heavy enough?

16:31.157 --> 16:33.075
<i>‐ Alright, y'all, rehearsal's up!</i>

16:33.367 --> 16:38.080
GUST: <i>At last, Hair‐aldine returns to us</i>
<i>from the big city.</i>

16:38.414 --> 16:41.751
‐ Alright, Val, this is the opening scene,

16:41.918 --> 16:44.795
so you need to make
your entrance powerful.

16:45.379 --> 16:46.756
‐ Powerful. Got it.

16:47.632 --> 16:48.466
[ Poppy gasps ]

16:48.466 --> 16:50.343
‐ I think I see her now.

16:52.136 --> 16:54.931
‐ Hair‐aldine in the house!

16:54.931 --> 16:56.432
Yeow!

16:57.099 --> 16:57.934
Power!

16:58.476 --> 16:59.310
Power!

16:59.685 --> 17:02.396
Power, power! Po‐po‐power!

17:04.440 --> 17:05.524
Power!

17:06.734 --> 17:09.737
[ clatter ]

17:12.740 --> 17:14.242
It's your line. Pfft.

17:15.159 --> 17:16.452
‐ Oh...

17:18.079 --> 17:19.288
All right!

17:19.288 --> 17:20.748
Everyone, take five.

17:22.208 --> 17:24.001
Val, a word...

17:25.670 --> 17:27.296
Perhaps you were right, Val,

17:27.797 --> 17:30.925
maybe musical theater isn't your thing.

17:31.425 --> 17:34.220
‐ Wait. Seriously?
You don't want me to do it anymore?

17:34.637 --> 17:35.471
‐ Well...

17:35.763 --> 17:39.267
I still believe you and Hair‐aldine
share the same fire, but...

17:40.017 --> 17:42.270
I guess it just wasn't meant to be.

17:42.270 --> 17:43.104
So...

17:43.479 --> 17:44.981
you're off the hook, sugar.

17:46.774 --> 17:47.817
C'mon, Synth.

17:47.817 --> 17:50.486
Maybe we can squeeze act three
on your left flipper.

17:52.029 --> 17:52.863
‐ Yes!

17:53.823 --> 17:56.200
You heard her, Popsqueak!
Deal is a deal!

17:56.826 --> 17:57.743
[ sigh ]

17:57.743 --> 18:01.455
‐ Yeah, if Holly says you're off the hook,
I guess you get the pass.

18:02.039 --> 18:05.876
But, Val, it feels to me
like your heart wasn't really in this.

18:05.876 --> 18:08.629
When we tell a friend
that we'll do something for them,

18:08.629 --> 18:10.715
it's important that we actually try to‐‐

18:11.716 --> 18:13.593
‐ Okay! Great lesson!

18:13.593 --> 18:14.635
Bye!

18:15.136 --> 18:15.970
‐ Ugh.

18:18.681 --> 18:21.392
‐ Wait! I'm next! I have a pass!

18:21.892 --> 18:23.102
[ trolls gasp ]

18:23.728 --> 18:25.730
Yeah!

18:26.230 --> 18:27.106
Woohoo!

18:27.773 --> 18:31.485
You really can see everything from here,
Classical Crest...

18:31.944 --> 18:33.321
Techno Lagoon...

18:33.779 --> 18:35.698
My friend, worried that the musical

18:35.698 --> 18:38.492
she worked so hard on
isn't gonna be as good as she hoped‐‐

18:38.826 --> 18:39.660
Wait.

18:40.745 --> 18:41.787
‐ Oh...

18:41.787 --> 18:45.333
♪

18:47.168 --> 18:50.129
‐ Hey! I said don't touch my guitar!

18:50.463 --> 18:52.381
ROCK TROLL:
Sorry again, Val!

18:52.381 --> 18:58.387
♪

18:59.930 --> 19:02.266
‐ Well... I guess this is it, y'all.

19:02.558 --> 19:03.392
Places!

19:04.644 --> 19:05.728
You ready, Synth?

19:06.354 --> 19:08.939
‐ Nah, yo, I'm very much terrified.

19:08.939 --> 19:10.024
Ha, ha!

19:10.733 --> 19:11.692
[ sigh ]

19:16.113 --> 19:18.824
GUST:
I thought this day would never come.

19:18.991 --> 19:23.663
At last, Hair‐aldine returns to us
from the big city.

19:25.164 --> 19:27.166
‐ I think I see her now.

19:30.670 --> 19:31.837
‐ Huh?
‐ Huh?

19:31.837 --> 19:33.089
[ confused murmurs ]

19:33.297 --> 19:34.298
‐ Uh...

19:34.298 --> 19:35.508
I said...

19:35.508 --> 19:37.718
I think I see her now!

19:40.262 --> 19:41.514
[ whimper ]

19:44.308 --> 19:46.352
‐ Yee‐haw!

19:46.352 --> 19:48.562
Hair‐aldine has arrived!

19:49.355 --> 19:52.024
[ cheering ]

19:52.024 --> 19:53.234
[ gasp ]

19:53.234 --> 19:56.153
[ cheering ]

19:58.531 --> 20:03.035
‐ By order of law,
I hereby ban all hair products.

20:03.035 --> 20:08.082
All sprays, gels and pomades
must be turned in by sundown!

20:08.374 --> 20:11.001
‐ Let's go wrangle up
all that stuff in here.

20:11.001 --> 20:12.753
‐ What do we do, Hair‐aldine?

20:14.755 --> 20:16.590
‐ We spray, dear sister.

20:16.799 --> 20:19.760
We get down on our knees and spray!

20:21.262 --> 20:24.890
And to that little girl, I say, "Rise."

20:25.266 --> 20:29.812
You spray and you curl
and you tease that hair!

20:29.979 --> 20:32.565
And when you feel you can't possibly make

20:32.565 --> 20:36.360
another brush stroke,
then, by Troll, you tease again!

20:37.278 --> 20:40.030
Because the only thing
bigger than your hair

20:40.406 --> 20:42.408
should be your dreams!

20:42.408 --> 20:45.828
[ crowd cheering ]

20:46.412 --> 20:50.624
‐ Now, it's hard for a Troll like me
to change his ways.

20:51.667 --> 20:53.252
But Hairaldine Groundwater,

20:53.794 --> 20:57.089
your passion for hairspray
has added volume,

20:57.298 --> 21:00.301
luster and bounce to my heart...

21:00.593 --> 21:02.678
and my head.

21:05.765 --> 21:07.266
‐ Oh, Pa!

21:07.266 --> 21:11.812
♪

21:12.354 --> 21:18.194
[ cheering ]

21:18.194 --> 21:19.403
‐ Holly, we did it!

21:19.945 --> 21:23.157
‐ Thanks for coming back
and putting your heart into this, Val.

21:23.157 --> 21:25.201
Hair‐aldine would be proud.

21:25.659 --> 21:26.786
I know I am.

21:29.371 --> 21:30.748
‐ Alright, alright...

21:30.998 --> 21:32.958
I've got a showstopping song to sing...

21:33.501 --> 21:34.335
ya'll.

21:35.961 --> 21:41.091
♪ When you believe in your dreams ♪

21:41.091 --> 21:44.929
♪ Never hold back ♪

21:44.929 --> 21:45.846
♪ Uh ♪

21:45.846 --> 21:50.142
♪ If you believe
You can make a difference ♪

21:50.142 --> 21:56.190
♪ Then take a stand
Raise your voice and sing ♪

21:56.190 --> 21:59.068
♪ We got big hair and bigger dreams ♪

21:59.068 --> 22:01.111
♪ Raise your voice and sing with me ♪

22:01.111 --> 22:02.988
♪ Oh, yay, yay ♪

22:02.988 --> 22:04.907
♪ Oh, yay, yay ♪

22:04.907 --> 22:07.743
♪ When they all try to keep us down ♪

22:07.743 --> 22:09.912
♪ We just pull our hairspray out ♪

22:09.912 --> 22:13.833
♪ And spray, spray ♪

22:13.833 --> 22:18.546
♪ It's about freedom
To be who we wanna be ♪

22:18.546 --> 22:22.299
♪ Hair in the air
So big and wild and free ♪

22:22.299 --> 22:25.219
♪ We've got big hair and bigger dreams ♪

22:25.219 --> 22:27.221
♪ So just pull your hairspray out ♪

22:27.221 --> 22:29.306
♪ And spray ♪

22:29.306 --> 22:34.436
♪ Spray with me ♪♪

22:34.436 --> 22:37.356
[ cheering ]

22:38.566 --> 22:40.317
♪ Cooper spins super ♪

22:40.317 --> 22:42.486
♪ Slapstick side splitting humor ♪

22:42.486 --> 22:46.490
♪ He's silly, straight killing us
With ridiculous bloopers ♪

22:46.490 --> 22:48.742
♪ He's our funny, funky, fabulous ♪

22:48.742 --> 22:50.661
♪ First place winner champion ♪

22:50.661 --> 22:52.955
♪ He's got jokes so fresh
He will impress ♪

22:52.955 --> 22:55.040
♪ This baby was born to win ♪

22:55.040 --> 22:57.084
♪ Try not to laugh, but you won't last ♪

22:57.084 --> 22:59.003
♪ He's hilarious till the end ♪

22:59.003 --> 23:01.297
♪ He's our funny, funky, fabulous ♪

